Let <img src="//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/1/7/4/174fadd07fd54c9afe288e96558c92e0c1da733a.png" class="latex" alt="$n$" width="10" height="8"> be a positive integer. In how many ways can a <img src="//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/5/0/6/506365464bf6cc349d99582ab3a8701137d6ee40.png" class="latex" alt="$4 \times 4n$" style="vertical-align: 0px" width="51" height="12"> grid be tiled with the following tetromino?<br>
